Requirements : 
** tweepy 	https://github.com/joshthecoder/tweepy
** osmgpsmap 0.7 	https://github.com/nzjrs/osm-gps-map
** python-flickrapi 	http://stuvel.eu/flickrapi
** BeautifulSoup 	http://www.crummy.com/software/BeautifulSoup/
** pyexiv2 >=0.2.2	http://tilloy.net/dev/pyexiv2/
** python-configobj
** python-simplejson


Ubuntu 10.10
---------------------

Semi-Automatic way (Recommended):


Install tweepy :

# easy_install tweepy

Download and install the .deb package from https://github.com/ilektrojohn/creepy/downloads .

Alternatively add creepy's ppa with :

$ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:jkakavas/creepy

update the package list :

$ sudo apt-get update

and install creepy with :

$ sudo apt-get install creepy

creepy is now on the main menu, under Applications -> Internet


Manual way (Deprecated - not recommended:)

Install dependenies first 

osmgpsmap:
#apt-get install python-osmgpsmap


tweepy:
Follow the instructions here :
https://github.com/joshthecoder/tweepy/blob/master/INSTALL

For the impatient amongst you try:
#apt-get install python-setuptools
#easy_install tweepy

flickrapi
#apt-get install python-flickrapi

BeautifulSoup
#apt-get install python-beautifulsoup

pyexiv2
# apt-get install python-pyexiv2

python-configobj
#apt-get install python-configobj

python-configobj
#apt-get install python-simplejson




Backtrack 4 ( R2 ) 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The situation for backtrack is not as plug and play but it can be resolved. The major problems
were with pyexiv2 and python-osmgpsmap . python-osmgpsmap is not in the repositores, and for pyexiv2 
version that exists is incompatible with creepy. To cut a long story short these are the detailed instructions 
to make it work :

### Install necessary packages from repositories

# apt-get install python-gtk2-dev libsoup2.4-dev libboost-python1.35-dev scons

Download ,compile and install exiv2 from source ( only v0.20 tested and working , maybe 0.19 also but not sure )
# wget http://exiv2.org/exiv2-0.20.tar.gz
# tar xvfz exiv2-0.20.tar.gz
# cd exiv2-0.20/
# ./configure
# make && make install

Download, compile and install pyexiv2 ( again only v0.2.2 tested and working, maybe v0.2.5 also but not sure )
# wget http://launchpad.net/pyexiv2/0.2.x/0.2.2/+download/pyexiv2-0.2.2.tar.bz2
# tar jxf pyexiv2-0.2.2.tar.bz2
# cd pyexiv2-0.2.2/
# scons
# scons install

I have no idea how to pass arguments to scons , so after that we must add /us/local/lib to our ld.so.conf
# echo 'include /usr/local/lib' >> /etc/ld.so.conf
# ldconfig

Download compile and install osmgpsmap and the python bindings
# wget http://www.johnstowers.co.nz/files/osm-gps-map/osm-gps-map-0.7.2.tar.gz
# tar xvfz osm-gps-map-0.7.2.tar.gz
# cd osm-gps-map-0.7.2/
# ./configure --prefix=/usr
# make && make install

# wget http://www.johnstowers.co.nz/files/osm-gps-map/python-osmgpsmap-0.7.2.tar.gz
# tar xvfz osm-gps-map/python-osmgpsmap-0.7.2.tar.gz
# cd osm-gps-map/python-osmgpsmap-0.7.2/
# ./configure --prefix=/usr
# make && make install


Install python modules needed : 
# easy_install flickrapi beautifulsoup configobj tweepy simplejson

Download creepy from github, unpack and run 
# python creepymap.py
